Gan Peck Cheng (simplified Chinese: 颜碧贞; traditional Chinese: 顏碧貞; pinyin: Yán Bìzhēn) is a Malaysian politician of Chinese descent. She is also the Johor state assemblywomen for Penggaram, Batu Pahat, Johor. She is a member of Democratic Action Party (DAP), a component of Pakatan Harapan (PH) coalition.
She was elected as the Opposition Chief of the Johor State Legislative Assembly since 27 October 2015 to replace Dr. Boo Cheng Hau who had resign.


